        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 9:13AM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 912 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Longwood University, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles. Reduced visibility and minor flooding possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Rice around 920 AM EDT.
Crewe around 940 AM EDT.
Jetersville around 945 AM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Maplewood, Moran,
Fergusonville, Jennings Ordinary, Stoddert, and Deatonville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
